{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"11a9b49e-2142-4674-ac56-a29d231f1be9","content":"Use **`dotnet run`**, not `dotnet test`.\n\nThe `Microsoft.Testing.Extensions.HotReload` package works with the **Microsoft Testing Platform** runner, which is activated via `dotnet run`. When you use `dotnet run`, it launches the test project as an executable, watches for file changes, and re-runs affected tests automatically.\n\n`dotnet test` uses the classic VSTest pipeline and does **not** support hot reload.\n\nTo start:\n\n```bash\nTESTINGPLATFORM_HOTRELOAD_ENABLED=1 dotnet run\n```\n\n(You mentioned you already set the environment variable, so just `dotnet run` should work.)","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"9733a853-5c5f-4fc0-af33-964a59c0c182","outputTokens":149,"requestId":"202E:2B8468:3814814:3DCC7F5:6A02EBC8"},"id":"0c33bd1f-094f-4223-9829-07d17ceb1885","timestamp":"2026-05-12T08:59:01.769Z","parentId":"01fe870e-1ef5-41c7-855b-40adadc42221"}
